@mention notification emails currently use the word 'Confluence' instead of site name:
{{./com/atlassian/confluence/plugins/mentions/MentionsI18n.properties:mention.mail.hint=<strong>Hint:</strong> You can mention somebody in Confluence by typing @ and then their name}}

Since users in most environments refer to the wiki site by its title, not the term 'Confluence', it would make sense to have this template to use the site title as well.

*Workaround*
Find the mentions plugin in your Confluence installation directory ({{<CONFLUENCE-INSTALL>/confluence/WEB-INF/atlassian-bundled-plugins/confluence-mentions-plugin-X.X.X.jar}}), unpack it, edit the contents you wish to modify and repack it, then place it back to the original location as of [https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONFKB/How+to+Edit+Files+in+Confluence+JAR+Files].

The exact line you have to edit for this is: {{./com/atlassian/confluence/plugins/mentions/MentionsI18n.properties:mention.mail.hint=<strong>Hint:</strong> You can mention somebody in Confluence by typing @ and then their name}}

